  "texts": [
    "Motivational framing refers to motivating people to participate in the social movement through calls to action.",
    "This paper addresses the broad question: how do people accomplish diagnostic, prognostic, and motivational core framing tasks on Twitter?",
    "We analyze a dataset of 1.85M tweets from movements in 2018-2019 surrounding three issue areas: guns, immigration, and LGBTQ rights, primarily within the U.S. context.",
    "We first develop a codebook, which we use to manually annotate a sample of 6,000 tweets for relevance, stance, and diagnostic, prognostic, and motivational framing strategies.",
    "We then use supervised machine learning techniques to infer labels for the rest of the tweets in our dataset."
  ],
